      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>In the next chapter we’ll look at <i>cycloalkanes</i>—saturated cyclic hydrocarbons—and we’ll see that the molecules generally adopt puckered, nonplanar conformations. Cyclohexane, for instance, has a puckered shape like a lounge chair rather than a flat shape. Why?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdjBRIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--2873dada26e022694430016a69d0357a599f5c37/OChem_03_EC_009.jpg\" alt=\"The chemical structures of non-planar cyclohexane and planar cyclohexane is represented.\">",
